    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/2332</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Alexandria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At the request of Red Cross ask British authorities if they can provide quick
                    transportation to Saloniki for cargo discharged from <persName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Caesar</hi>
                    </persName>. If transportation can be provided make immediate arrangements to
                    forward all serviceable cargo for relief situation Saloniki.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d672fn1">In a telegram of Sept. 25 the Consul reported: “Entire
                        consignment now loading.” (File No. 811.142/2391.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
